properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued February 6 at 3:28AM EST until February 7 at 1:00PM EST by NWS Miami FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest winds 15 to 25 kt with gusts up to 30 kt and
seas 5 to 8 feet expected.

* WHERE...In Gulf of Mexico, Coastal waters from East Cape Sable
to Chokoloskee FL out 20 NM, Coastal waters from Chokoloskee
to Bonita Beach FL out 20 NM and Waters from Chokoloskee to
Bonita Beach FL from 20 to 60 NM. In Lake Okeechobee, Lake
Okeechobee. In Biscayne Bay, Biscayne Bay.

* WHEN...From 7 AM this morning to 1 PM EST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced mariners, especially those operating smaller
vessels, should avoid navigating in hazardous conditions.

A sudden onset of rough seas may cause hazardous conditions,
which may occur suddenly at jetties and inlets. These conditions
could catch boaters by surprise. Boaters should use caution when
entering or exiting the inlets and jetty areas.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 7 AM THIS MORNING TO 1 PM EST FRIDAY
